getTaskQueueFlushRatio

@GridMBeanDescription(value="Task queue flush ratio.")
float getTaskQueueFlushRatio()
Gets task queue flush ratio.

This parameter is used to calculate flush size of the queue. When the size of the queue exceeds GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean.getTaskQueueCapacity() * getTaskQueueFlushRatio() then worker threads are waken up and start to perform asynchronous task processing.

Returns:
Task queue flush ratio.

getTaskQueueFlushFrequency

@GridMBeanDescription(value="Task queue flush frequency.")
int getTaskQueueFlushFrequency()
Gets task queue flush frequency.

Each worker thread will wait at most this amount of milliseconds before it starts to process tasks. Note, however, that if queue size exceeds GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean.getTaskQueueCapacity() * GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean.getTaskQueueFlushRatio(), then worker threads will wake up immediately.

Returns:
Task queue flush frequency in milliseconds.

getSyncDelay

@GridMBeanDescription(value="Sync delay.")
int getSyncDelay()
Gets sync delay in ms.

This property is critical for evictions.

When SPI writes entry to file it does not force underlying storage sync for better performance. Index entry for corresponding swap entry is written with System.currentTimeMillis() timestamp. There probably can be a delay before all OS buffers associated with entry file are flushed and actual file modification date may be a bit greater than one in the index. If index timestamp + syncDelay is greater tha file modification date, then index entry is considered to be valid and file can be evicted.

Returns:
Sync delay.
